
              Converting your Chiara to ROS

***********************************************************
STEP 1 - upgrade Ubuntu from 8.04 to 10.04 (LTS release)

 1) ssh into the robot
 2) run "sudo apt-get update"
 3) check that /etc/update-manager/release-upgrades includes
    the following lines:
      
        [DEFAULT]
        Prompt=lts

 4) run "sudo-release-upgrade" -- *this will take some time*
 5) check that /boot/grub/menu.lst has the 10.04 kernel at 
    the top, before rebooting the Chiara.

After upgrading, you may have to reconfigure the wifi again
for it to work properly. 

***********************************************************
STEP 2 - Install ROS
 
 1) follow directions found on: 
      http://www.ros.org/wiki/cturtle/Installation/Ubuntu
    and install "ros-cturtle-base"
 
***********************************************************
STEP 3 - Install Chiara Specific ROS files

 1) install from rosinstall .... ?
 2) patch arbotix for cturtle .... 
 3) 

